  "text": "The boundary conditions (2.4a) and (2.4b) must currently be met for ρ = R and ρ = R + d. It is, however, a well-known fact [20, [CITATION_1] that this set of requirements is inconsistent unless we put m = 0 (it is the depolarization effect, which leads to mixing T E z and T M z waves). We recall this fact here since it does not appear in the two-dimensional model.",
